    <div class="prose">
      <p>Stopping reconciliation from failing for good is two jobs: repairing the damage already in the books, and building a process so it doesn&rsquo;t recur. The repair is finding and unwinding the forced adjustments, locating the real differences they hid, correcting a wrong opening balance, and re-running each month until it ties to the statement. The process is everything that keeps it tied afterward &mdash; a fixed monthly cadence, locked reconciled periods, reviewed bank feeds, and one accountable owner of the close. A Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor with active Online and Desktop certifications does both against a written scope. Independent firm &mdash; not Intuit, and not Intuit&rsquo;s software support; an Intuit account, login, or billing matter stays with Intuit.</p>
